Item 3. Legal Proceedings
SEC regulations require us to disclose certain information about environmental proceedings if a governmental authority is a party
to such proceedings and such proceedings involve potential monetary sanctions that we reasonably believe will exceed a stated
threshold. Pursuant to the SEC regulations, the Company will use a threshold of $1 million for purposes of determining whether
disclosure of any such proceedings is required.
The discussion under Note 16 to our consolidated financial statements is incorporated by reference into this Part I, Item 3.
