service and compensation history. Accrual of defined pension benefits ceased in 2012 for U.S. and Canadian salaried employees.
There is also an unfunded nonqualified pension plan primarily covering U.S. executives for service prior to January 1, 2007 and it is
based on an “excess plan” for service after that date.
The funding policy for qualified defined benefit pension plans is to contribute annually not less than the minimum required by
applicable laws and regulations or to directly pay benefit payments where appropriate. In the year ended December 31, 2022 all legal
funding requirements were met. The following table summarizes contributions made to the defined benefit pension plans:
